AFRICAN SWINE FEVER - UKRAINE (02): (LUHANSK) SPREAD SUSPECTED, REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
**********************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 13 Jan 2014
Source: Segodnya.ua [in Russian, machine trans., edited]
http://www.segodnya.ua/regions/donetsk/v-lugansk-prishla-afrikanskaya-chuma-488198.html


During an inter-ministerial meeting with representatives of the Russian Federation today (13 Jan 2014), it was revealed that 2 cases of African swine fever [ASF] have been reported from the Luhansk oblast [region of Ukraine], near the border with Russia.

According to the press service of the regional State Service for Emergency Situations ["GSCHS"], units stationed in the border areas have been put on alert. "In the event of an outbreak of the plague [ASF], increased services will be provided by other units," said the administration.

The 1st ASF incident was reported on 5 Jan 2014. The specialised diagnostic laboratory of the State Scientific Research Institute confirmed the diagnosis of ASF after analyses of samples collected from the corpse of a dead wild boar, found in the river Derkul separating the territories of Ukraine and Russia. 3 villages in the region have been put under quarantine.

[byline: Anton Glushkov]

--
communicated by:
Sabine Zentis
