[Luhansk oblast (region) is situated in east Ukraine, bordering the Rostov oblast of the Russian Federation; see political map at http://www.mapsofworld.com/ukraine/ukraine-political-map.html. It is not clear if the new (suspected?) cases have been recorded in domestic swine or in wild boars.

On 8 Jan 2014, Ukraine reported to the OIE the discovery of an ASF-infected wild boar, in the river Derkul. The locations of the said case, of the previous ASF case in (south) Ukraine (September 2012), and of ASF outbreaks in the region and particularly in neighbouring Rostov oblast, since 2011, can be seen on OIE's map at http://tinyurl.com/q2pmbbb (click on eastern Ukraine; when centered, zoom in).

A confirmation -- or otherwise -- of new ASF cases in Luhansk will be appreciated. In case confirmed, additional information is requested, including the identity -- domestic pig or wild boars -- of the affected swine. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/9OP2.]
